Male.
Abdominal sternite 8 with moderately wide and deep, obtuse medioapical emargination. Sternite 9 short and wide; apical margin straight, without apical emargination; tapered basal portion moderately long (
Fig. 1-2 G
). Tergite 10 shovel-like, with widely rounded apex, sparsely setose (
Fig. 1-2 D
). Aedeagus simple in ventral view, but with a fin-shaped protuberance in middle portion in lateral view (
Figs. 1-1 B, C, 1-2 A–C
); apical portion of paramere shaped as in 
Figs. 1-1 D, 1-2 E
, with sensory peg setae arranged along lateral sides, not numerous.
